						<div class="postbody">About old CRT TVs, my mother got a new HD TV in her room a while ago and, even though I pleaded her not to, she replaced the old CRT with a new HD TV with the delusion that 20+ year old systems are going to look better on it. Sure enough, my NES Zapper didn't work then and the game was slightly ahead than what was onscreen. Both are due to processing the analogue signal and transferring it into a digital signal or something. (I've heard of fancy box things you can use to decrease the transfer time, but I think I remember seeing one on line for $200) It was about time for the old TV to go though, because the table it was on was literally bending under its weight!<br /><br />(Just felt like sharing that.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> )</div>

