					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To be clear about the box the Super Scope comes with, it's just an IR receiver. The front of the Scope transmits data like a remote via IR to the box. I guess they wanted to avoid wires. It has nothing to do with detecting the position the Scope is aimed at. <br /><br />The SNES has a special latching feature accessible from the controller port. The Super Scope uses it I believe. Software can trigger the latch as well. Lookup register $4201. The Konami Justifier lightguns might use it as well.</div>

